article.headline: North Dakota 56, Bowling Green 53
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Jamal Webb's 3-pointer with 43 seconds gave North Dakota the lead for good in a 56-53 victory over Bowling Green Friday night. Troy Huff, who finished with 14 points and 12 rebounds, made two free throws with 15 seconds left for the game's final points. The Falcons missed a chance to tie in the closing seconds. Webb scored 12 points for North Dakota(3-8). Jordon Crawford led Bowling Green (5-7) with 14 points. Crawford hit a 3-pointer with 2:44 left to get the Falcons within 51-50, and Richaun Holmes' three-point play with a minute remaining gave Bowling Green a 53-51 lead before Webb's 3-pointer. A'uston Calhoun had 12 points and a team-high eight rebounds for BGSU, and Holmes finished with 10 points and six blocked shots.
